The article discusses the recent gun violence incidents in Dadeville, Alabama and Louisville, where several people were killed and many others injured. It highlights the concern about the safety of children attending events like birthday parties and the worry parents have when their children leave the house. The article emphasizes that guns are the leading cause of death for children in America and calls for lawmakers to take action on gun safety reforms. It criticizes Republican leaders for supporting laws that undermine gun safety and praises Tennessee Governor Bill Lee for signing an Executive Order to expand background checks and urging the statehouse to pass a red flag law. The author calls for federal legislation to require safe firearm storage, universal background checks, elimination of gun manufacturers' immunity from liability, and a ban on assault weapons and high-capacity magazines.